<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro digest_ext_error(da) is defined as the constant expression (false). Any call if (digest_ext_error(&da)) { ret = MHD_NO; } can never be true, so the assignment ret = MHD_NO (and the whole conditional branch) is code that will never affect program behaviour and is therefore dead. For example, in MHD_digest_auth_calc_userdigest the#ifdef MHD_DIGEST_HAS_EXT_ERROR guarded check becomes a constant false test (when this macro definition is in effect), making the ret = MHD_NO path dead code. Removal of that conditional would not change behaviour (the argument &da has no side-effects), so Rule 2.2 is violated.
</scenario>
